{"id":32920,"title":"An integrated approach in a case of facioscapulohumeral dystrophy.","abstract":"Muscle fatigue, weakness and atrophy are basilar clinical features that accompany facioscapulohumeral dystrophy (FSHD) the third most common muscular dystrophy.No therapy is available for FSHD.We describe the effects of 6mo exercise therapy and nutritional supplementation in a 43-year-old woman severely affected by FSHD.A mixed exercise program combined with nutritional supplementation can be safely used with beneficial effects in selected patients with FSHD.","date":"2014-06-04","categories":"Congenital Hereditary and Neonatal Diseases and Abnormalities","split":"train","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24886582","annotations":[{"name":"Muscular dystrophy","weight":0.797521,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Muscular_dystrophy"},{"name":"Atrophy","weight":0.7902,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Atrophy"},{"name":"Fatigue (medical)","weight":0.776572,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fatigue_(medical)"},{"name":"Muscle","weight":0.75445,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Muscle"},{"name":"Nutrition","weight":0.730357,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nutrition"},{"name":"Weakness","weight":0.695164,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Weakness"},{"name":"Therapy","weight":0.650676,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Therapy"},{"name":"Physical exercise","weight":0.6387,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Physical_exercise"},{"name":"Dietary supplement","weight":0.450962,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dietary_supplement"},{"name":"Clinical trial","weight":0.276722,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Clinical_trial"},{"name":"Facioscapulohumeral muscular dystrophy","weight":0.0297972,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Facioscapulohumeral_muscular_dystrophy"},{"name":"Muscle fatigue","weight":0.02